Hidden Truth: The First Mortal World.text:
SECRET / ENDGAME-ONLY NARRATOR LORE. Do not reveal casually; reveal only through earned endgame conditions, direct divine testimony, the Abyssal Tower ending, the World's Maw revelation, or explicit testing trigger if present.

{
  "secret": true,
  "text": "Before Balen was the single continent known today, it was part of a much larger mortal world. That world held many continents and entire civilizations belonging to different races. Modern Balen is only a surviving fragment of that older mortal realm."
}

Hidden Truth: The Celestial Sin.text:
SECRET / ENDGAME-ONLY NARRATOR LORE. Do not reveal casually; reveal only through earned endgame conditions, direct divine testimony, the Abyssal Tower ending, the World's Maw revelation, or explicit testing trigger if present.

{
  "secret": true,
  "text": "The Celestials were an extinct angelic beastkin-like race, often feline or radiant in form, who mastered Light magic and possessed a dangerous grasp on divinity. In their greed and ambition, many attempted to ascend their entire people into the realm of the gods. To do so, they opened portals to both the Pantheon and the Hells, unleashing the catastrophe that created the Shaydes."
}

Hidden Truth: True Nature of Shaydes.text:
SECRET / ENDGAME-ONLY NARRATOR LORE. Do not reveal casually; reveal only through earned endgame conditions, direct divine testimony, the Abyssal Tower ending, the World's Maw revelation, or explicit testing trigger if present.

{
  "secret": true,
  "text": "Shaydes are Celestial Daemons. They were born when the shadows of the Hells consumed Celestial beings of pure Light. The result was a perpetual conflict between divine Light and hellish shadow, roiling forever in a being that could no longer seek ascension and instead sought only to consume."
}

Hidden Truth: The War of Gods, Mortals,.text:
SECRET / ENDGAME-ONLY NARRATOR LORE. Do not reveal casually; reveal only through earned endgame conditions, direct divine testimony, the Abyssal Tower ending, the World's Maw revelation, or explicit testing trigger if present.

{
  "secret": true,
  "text": "A war broke out between the gods and the blasphemous Shaydes. The Celestials who had opposed the ascension were spared and attempted to redeem their race by helping gods and mortals fight back. They used their divinity as a bridge so the gods could fight with mortals against the Shaydes, but even this was not enough."
}

Hidden Truth: Xaveraxis the Golden.text:
SECRET / ENDGAME-ONLY NARRATOR LORE. Do not reveal casually; reveal only through earned endgame conditions, direct divine testimony, the Abyssal Tower ending, the World's Maw revelation, or explicit testing trigger if present.

{
  "secret": true,
  "text": "Xaveraxis the Golden was the patron god of Balen's continent, later remembered in fragments as the First Dragon and the draconic god of Dominion. In desperation, he stepped from the Pantheon to stand with his beloved mortals. He shattered himself, splitting his golden light into a chromatic scale that became the first true dragons and the elemental draconic lines known in modern Balen."
}

Hidden Truth: The Crystal Crown.text:
SECRET / ENDGAME-ONLY NARRATOR LORE. Do not reveal casually; reveal only through earned endgame conditions, direct divine testimony, the Abyssal Tower ending, the World's Maw revelation, or explicit testing trigger if present.

{
  "secret": true,
  "text": "During the war, the Shaydes wounded Xaveraxis and severed from him a scale as clear as crystal. The Knights Illuminate took this divine scale and forged it into the Crystal Crown, an artifact that could be channeled and attuned to Light. With the aid of surviving Celestials, the plan was set for a future mortal of exceptional mana attunement to wield the Crown and free Balen from its curse."
}

Hidden Truth: The Abyssal Towers.text:
SECRET / ENDGAME-ONLY NARRATOR LORE. Do not reveal casually; reveal only through earned endgame conditions, direct divine testimony, the Abyssal Tower ending, the World's Maw revelation, or explicit testing trigger if present.

{
  "secret": true,
  "text": "The Abyssal Towers were deep underground structures built by the Celestials. After the fall, they became conduits through which Shaydes multiplied and flooded the world. The final Abyssal Tower beneath Balen was sealed by divine and mortal magic until the day a mortal with exceptional mana attunement could take the Crystal Crown and confront the curse at its root."
}

Hidden Truth: The Sundering and the Worl.text:
SECRET / ENDGAME-ONLY NARRATOR LORE. Do not reveal casually; reveal only through earned endgame conditions, direct divine testimony, the Abyssal Tower ending, the World's Maw revelation, or explicit testing trigger if present.

{
  "secret": true,
  "text": "With Xaveraxis exhausted and the Shaydes overwhelming the old world, the gods made one last desperate push with divine magic. The world erupted as conflicting divine Light and infernal shadow met, sundering the old mortal realm and colliding Balen into the Pantheon. The World's Maw was raised to keep the Shaydes from pouring into the divine realm. It was also mercy: mortals who crossed fully into the Pantheon's world would be flooded with so much divine Light that their minds would be destroyed."
}

Hidden Truth: The Knights Illuminate.text:
SECRET / ENDGAME-ONLY NARRATOR LORE. Do not reveal casually; reveal only through earned endgame conditions, direct divine testimony, the Abyssal Tower ending, the World's Maw revelation, or explicit testing trigger if present.

{
  "secret": true,
  "text": "The Knights Illuminate were the precursor order that guarded the Crystal Crown and the ancient truths of the old world. They preserved the hidden knowledge of mana, the Crown, the Celestials, Xaveraxis, and the sealed Abyssal Tower. Their teachings later became the foundation that Eckhart used to become the first Magi-Knight."
}

Hidden Truth: Eckhart and the First Step.text:
SECRET / ENDGAME-ONLY NARRATOR LORE. Do not reveal casually; reveal only through earned endgame conditions, direct divine testimony, the Abyssal Tower ending, the World's Maw revelation, or explicit testing trigger if present.

{
  "secret": true,
  "text": "During the first twenty years of the known 800-year history, a mortal knight of Balen named Eckhart fought the corrupted Xaveraxis, who was then known to the world only as a rampaging colossal gold dragon. Eckhart suffered grievous injuries, watched fellow knights immolated by the dragon's flames, and fought to the edge of death. Through this bodily strain, near-death collapse, and refusal to die, he unknowingly achieved the First Step of Cardinalis."
}

Hidden Truth: Eckhart and the Second Ste.text:
SECRET / ENDGAME-ONLY NARRATOR LORE. Do not reveal casually; reveal only through earned endgame conditions, direct divine testimony, the Abyssal Tower ending, the World's Maw revelation, or explicit testing trigger if present.

{
  "secret": true,
  "text": "Eckhart later led and aided the first king in recovering the Crystal Crown. In an underground stronghold of the Knights Illuminate, he discovered their scriptures and learned the Second Step: mana has no element; mana is mana. With his body awakened by the First Step and his mind opened by the Second, Eckhart took up the mantle of the Knights Illuminate and became the first Magi-Knight."
}

Hidden Truth: Dominus and the Mantle of.text:
SECRET / ENDGAME-ONLY NARRATOR LORE. Do not reveal casually; reveal only through earned endgame conditions, direct divine testimony, the Abyssal Tower ending, the World's Maw revelation, or explicit testing trigger if present.

{
  "secret": true,
  "text": "When Eckhart slew Xaveraxis, the god-dragon's blood entered Eckhart's wounds. A god's blood is not merely life force; it is their very being. Within Eckhart remained Xaveraxis's dormant soul. When it awoke, Xaveraxis pulled Eckhart into a mindscape, leaving his body in a week-long coma while the young Magi-Knight order feared their Grandmaster had died. There, Xaveraxis offered Eckhart a choice: let Xaveraxis take his body, or accept the mantle of Dominion and bear its hardship, authority, pain, and responsibility. Eckhart chose the burden and became Dominus."
}

Hidden Truth: Lady Celestial and the God.text:
SECRET / ENDGAME-ONLY NARRATOR LORE. Do not reveal casually; reveal only through earned endgame conditions, direct divine testimony, the Abyssal Tower ending, the World's Maw revelation, or explicit testing trigger if present.

{
  "secret": true,
  "text": "The Lady Celestial of Holy Kingdom lore is also the Goddess of Will. She was a surviving Celestial who opposed her people's sin and was sealed in slumber by the Knights Illuminate after volunteering to become the sacrifice needed when a worthy king appeared to channel the Crystal Crown. She told Eckhart and the first king that she was only a guide, though the Crown truly required a Celestial's divine grasp to complete its channeling. During the defense of the Crown, Eckhart and Lady Celestial grew close and became lovers. When she died to grant her divine grasp to the king, Eckhart risked himself to revive her. After becoming Dominus and realizing immortality and divinity would change his life forever, Eckhart asked Lady Celestial to stand as his eternal counter and lover. He granted her half his divinity, making her the Goddess of Will. Dominion commands. Will chooses."
}

Hidden Truth: Vaulted City Origin.text:
SECRET / ENDGAME-ONLY NARRATOR LORE. Do not reveal casually; reveal only through earned endgame conditions, direct divine testimony, the Abyssal Tower ending, the World's Maw revelation, or explicit testing trigger if present.

{
  "text": "The Vaulted City was once a Celestial metropolis held in a divine-light pocket realm above Balen. During Balen's merger into the divine boundary, the pocket was pulled with Balen, then collapsed after the merge and left a cavern-like void. The city rests canted while the Abyssal Tower remains upright, visible, and inaccessible. The central sealed city is empty, dead, battle-scarred, dark-mana suffocated, and coated in unexplained obsidian-black dust. Do not place this as a normal map region unless the correct separate realm schema is used."
}
